# [IPPM](../wg/ippm.html)

## Summary

The IPPM and BMWG working groups held a joint session at IETF 126 in Vienna to discuss active working group drafts, proposed work, and the ongoing effort to merge the two groups under a single joint charter. 

Key milestones highlighted during the session include several documents progressing to the RFC Editor queue (Quality of Outcome, Asymmetrical Packets, and various BMWG milestones), updates on active drafts such as connectivity monitoring and responsiveness, and a structured discussion on the joint charter proposal, including implementation policies and potential names for the merged working group.

