### 6. In-Network Telemetry Aggregation Using IOAM Aggregation Trace and Template Options
* **Presenter:** **Alexander Clemm**
* **Slides:** [4. In-Network Telemetry Aggregation Using IOAM Aggregation Trace and Template Options](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-ippm-sessb-3-in-network-telemetry-aggregation-using-ioam-aggregation-trace-and-template-options-02)
* **Discussion:**
  * This work explores preprocessing telemetry data (min, max, sum) *during* packet traversal (in-network aggregation) rather than collecting raw records from each individual node.
  * Hackathon efforts focused on comparing the trace and template options, extending proof-of-concepts (e.g., a network sustainability carbon-tracking case by OST Switzerland and a Linux kernel implementation by the University of Rome), and designing a combined "trace plus template" option that saves 8 bytes of packet overhead.
  * **Giuseppe Fioccola** and **Frank Brockners** discussed whether other proposed IOAM extensions in IPPM should align with this template option to prevent option sprawl. **Frank Brockners** supported working group adoption of the template draft to create a streamlined foundation similar to IPFIX.
  * A poll was taken regarding document familiarity:
    * **Poll:** *Did you read the presented document?*
      * Yes: 7, No: 17, No opinion: 2 (Total: 70)

