## Joint Charter Discussion and WG Polls

* **Presenter:** **Ching Wu**
* **Slides:** [7. Feedback on IPPM/BMWG Joint Charter Proposal](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-ippm-feedback-on-ippmbmwg-joint-charter-proposal-00)

**Ching Wu** presented the proposed joint charter for the combined working group, summarizing feedback received since IETF 125. The draft charter avoids strict separation between production and lab-based applicability, integrates IPFIX and YANG management aspects, and emphasizes calibration and transport scalability.

### Implementation Policy
To maintain high-quality specifications, the joint charter proposal evaluated three options for standardizing implementations:
* **Option 1:** Prioritize documents with existing implementations.
* **Option 2:** Require at least one implementation for Standards Track documents.
* **Option 3:** Require at least two implementations for Standards Track documents.
* **Outcome:** There was general agreement to adopt **Option 2**.

### Joint Working Group Name Polls
A series of polls were conducted to gauge preference for the name of the merged working group:

1. **Poll:** *Please vote "YES" if you favor "BPM" as the name of the joint working group name. If you believe this name should not be chosen, vote "NO" and speak up with the reason why not.*
   * Yes: 17, No: 1, No opinion: 14 (Total: 72)
   * *Discussion:* **Tim Chown** voted NO, expressing concern that "BPM" sounds like "beats per minute." **Jared Mauch** questioned what the letters would stand for.
2. **Poll:** *Please vote "YES" if you favor "BIPP" as the name of the joint working group name. If you believe this name should not be chosen, vote "NO" and speak up with the reason why not.*
   * Yes: 2, No: 13, No opinion: 8 (Total: 72)
3. **Poll:** *Please vote "YES" if you favor "BMPM" as the name of the joint working group name. If you believe this name should not be chosen, vote "NO" and speak up with the reason why not.*
   * Yes: 12, No: 3, No opinion: 6 (Total: 72)
4. **Poll:** *Please vote "YES" if you favor "NETMEASURE" as the name of the joint working group name. If you believe this name should not be chosen, vote "NO" and speak up with the reason why not.*
   * Yes: 3, No: 16, No opinion: 4 (Total: 72)
5. **Poll:** *Please vote "YES" if you favor "BPMP" as the name of the joint working group name. If you believe this name should not be chosen, vote "NO" and speak up with the reason why not.*
   * Yes: 9, No: 14, No opinion: 4 (Total: 72)

**Decision:** The name preference will be finalized and confirmed on the mailing list, with "BPM" and "BMPM" showing the highest level of support.

